news.title: Telangana government prepares for forensic audit of land records
news.para: Telangana is gearing up for a forensic audit of its land records, with Telangana Technology Services Limited (TGTS) expected to sign an agreement with a Kerala-based security audit agency within a week. The audit will initially focus on suspicious land transactions in districts like Rangareddy and Hyderabad.

news.title: SC dismisses appeal challenging eviction orders issued by HYDRAA
news.para: The Supreme Court has dismissed businessman P Satya Narayana's appeal against eviction orders, affirming the Jubilee Hills House Building Cooperative Society's right to reclaim a 2,000-square-yard property in Jubilee Hills. This decision follows a Telangana High Court ruling that supported HYDRAA's eviction notices due to Satya Narayana's failure to provide ownership proof for the land.

news.title: States to be soon ranked on land record quality, ease of land acquisition for road projects
news.para: The government is set to rank states based on their land record quality, land acquisition ease, and highway project support. Delays in land acquisition and poor records significantly hinder road project execution. This ranking aims to address issues like 'missing plots' discovered post-approval, causing project standstills and prolonging completion timelines, as highlighted by the road transport and highways secretary.
